4865a5e6-e47f-45f1-ae0b-b19738c86edf.29e80869-2873-410d-bec9-4efe090c18ef.description=
Generates a random number.

Inputs\:
max - The maximum number that can be returned.
min - The minimum number that can be returned.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed Successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
A random number between max and min (inclusive)
4865a5e6-e47f-45f1-ae0b-b19738c86edf.b39bf881-a721-4bbf-9f0b-abcd030df3fb.description=The "How do I\: Use a multi-instance step" flow demonstrates how to a use multi-instance step, which operates on a list of values at the same time. To make a step into a multi-instance step, you right-click the step and then select "Toggle Multi-instance", then provide an input list with more than one value. To provide the input with multiple values, you specify that the input’s value is a list, then provide the list to the input. All of the transitions must connect back to the multi-instance step except for the "group done" transition. 
This flow was created using the following default OO operations\:
-  "FS Create Directory" from the Library/Operations/FileSystem/Cross Platform folder.
-  "Display Message" from the Library/Utility Operations folder.

The flow contains the following steps\:

1. The "FS Create Directory" step  has been changed to a multi-instance step with an input list that 
contains multiple values. The step creates thefolders in the list until the list is finished, then the 
"group done" transition proceeds to the next step.
      Input\: "path"
      Gets value from\: user prompt
      Places result in\:  flow variable "path"
          
2. The "Display Message" step displays a message to the user.
      Input\:  "message"
      Gets value from\: constant
          "The folder ${path} was created successfully."

This flow was created using the following OO operations\:
- “Random Number Generator” from the Library/Utility Operations folder
- “Get Current Date and Time” from the  Library/Utility Operations/Date and Time folder
- “Display Message” from the Library/Utility Operations folder

The flow contains the following steps\:

1. The parallel split step starts, running the two lanes simultaneously.     

2. The “Generate Random Number”  step generates a random number.
     Input\: "max"
     Gets value from\:  constant value “100”

     Input\: "min"
     Gets value from\:  constant value “1”
 
     Places result in\: flow variable "randomNumber" 

3. The “Get Current Date and Time” step captures the current date and time.
     Places result in\:   flow variable  “dateTime”

4. The “Display Message” step displays a message to the user.
     Input\:  message
     Gets value from\:  constant  
         " Parallel split step completed. 
         The current date/time is ${dateTime}.  
          A random number\: ${randomNumber}."
   
   Places result in\: default flow variable "message"
